Sentencas: A highly active anode material for solid oxide fuel cells resistant to carbon deposition is developed.
Titulo: A-Site Ordered Double Perovskite with in Situ Exsolved Core-Shell Nanoparticles as Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Co-Fe co-doped La0.5Ba0.5MnO3-delta with a cubic-hexagonal heterogeneous stucture is synthesized through the Pechini method.
Titulo: A-Site Ordered Double Perovskite with in Situ Exsolved Core-Shell Nanoparticles as Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: An A-site ordered double perovskite with Co0.94Fe0.06 alloy-oxide core-shell nanoparticles on its surface is formed after reduction.
Titulo: A-Site Ordered Double Perovskite with in Situ Exsolved Core-Shell Nanoparticles as Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The phase transition and the exsolution of the nanoparticles are investigated with X-ray diffraction, thermogravimetric analysis, and high-resolution transmission electron microscope.
Titulo: A-Site Ordered Double Perovskite with in Situ Exsolved Core-Shell Nanoparticles as Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The exsolved nanoparticles with the layered double-perovskite supporter show a high catalytic activity.
Titulo: A-Site Ordered Double Perovskite with in Situ Exsolved Core-Shell Nanoparticles as Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: A single cell with that anode and a 300 mu m thick La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta, electrolyte layer exhibits maximum power densities of 1479 and 503 mW cm(-2) at 850 degrees C with wet hydrogen and wet methane fuels, respectively.
Titulo: A-Site Ordered Double Perovskite with in Situ Exsolved Core-Shell Nanoparticles as Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Moreover, the single cell fed with wet methane exhibits a stable power output at 850 degrees C for 200 h, demonstrating a high resistance to carbon deposition of the anode due to the strong anchor of the exsolved nanoparticles on the perovskite parent.
Titulo: A-Site Ordered Double Perovskite with in Situ Exsolved Core-Shell Nanoparticles as Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The oxide shell also preserves the metal particles from coking.
Titulo: A-Site Ordered Double Perovskite with in Situ Exsolved Core-Shell Nanoparticles as Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
